1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using visual explanations to interpret the behavior of deep neural networks in self-driving cars. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for perception and control in self-driving cars. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of end-to-end learning and attention models for training the network. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper focuses on self-driving cars, which are a type of robot. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the importance of providing easy-to-interpret rationales for the behavior of self-driving cars, which is relevant to human-computer interaction.
